 producers of the movie are Aashiq Abu and Rajesh George Kulangara. The movie takes place in a coastal village, Chellanam, Kochi, and follows the story of the death and then the funeral of an older adult named Valiyathuparambil Vavachan Mesthiri, who belongs to the Latin Catholic Community. The film earned Best Director Awards at the 48th Kerela State Film Awards and 49th International Film Festival of India, as well as a Best Actor Award for Chembon Vinod at the latter ceremony. Furthermore, it won two more awards at the International Film Festival of Kerela. The film also made it to the list of the Best 25 Malayalam Films of the Decade by THE HINDU. It won several more awards as well and received amazing reviews for shedding the audience's tears. 10. Sudani from Nigeria (2018) This is a sports-based drama Malayalam movie. Zakariya Mohammed did the job of being a director and a writer for the film, although Muhsin Parari helped him to co-write dialogues. Sameer Thahir and Shyju Khalid produced the film. The main cast revolves around Majeed, who was played by Soubin Shahir, while Samuel Abiola Robinson played the character with the same name as his real one, who was a football player hailing from Nigeria. The movie's scene is set in a rural area of Malappuram, Kerela. The story revolves around these two people living in different areas who get connected because of their passion for football. They eventually face some setbacks and challenges on their way. The film won a total of 5 awards at the 2018 Kerela State Film Awards - Best Screenplay, a Best Film with Popular and Aesthetic Value, Best Actor, Best Character Actress, and Best Debut Actor. At the 2018 National Film Awards, it won another award for being the Best Feature Film in Malayalam. The film also made it to THE HINDU's List of 25 top Malayalam Movies of the Decade. The film received a positive critical response from the audience and the critics and was rated as one of the best movies made in the year. It w