ived a positive critical response from the audience and the critics and was rated as one of the best movies made in the year. It won a majority of the awards it got nominated for and won several of them. 11. Thondi Muthalum Driksakshiyum (2017) Directed by Dileesh Pothan and written by Sajeev Pazhoor, this Malayalam movie is a crime-based film. Sandip Senan and Anish M. Thomas jointly produced the film. The main cast of the film comprises Fahadh Faasil and Suraj Venjaramoodu, playing the roles of the thief Prasad and the farmer Prasad respectively. The thief steals a gold chain from the farmer and is then accused of swallowing it, and how the trial for him goes on. The movie earned a total of 36 awards, which includes three awards at the National Film Awards, four at the Filmfare Awards South, three at the South Indian International Movie Awards, two at the Kerala State Film Awards and many more. The film was praised for having exceptional 'Execution and Intelligence in the Flow.' The movie was regarded as almost perfect and something is never seen before. 12. Nayattu (2021) This is a political and thriller movie for those who are interested in the genre. Martin Prakkat has directed the film, while Shahi Kabir has written the film. It is produced by Ranjith, P. M. Sasidharan and the director Martin Prakkat collectively. The main cast in the movie is Kunchako Boban playing Praveen Michael (CPO), Joju George playing ASI Maniyan and Nimisha Sajayan as Sunitha (CPO). The movie brings out the helplessness of three police officers, CPO Maniyan, ASI Sunitha and CPO Praveen, who are on the run for their life after the death of a Dalit youth. This movie even made it to be on the shortlist as India's selection for the title of Best International Film at the 94th Academy Awards. The film received critical praise for the quality of work put in by its director and actors, as well as how it was very influential. Almost everyone who watched the film, whether they were a part of th