n as well as directed by Rajin Thomas. The main cast in the film consists of Sreenath Bhasi, Indrans, Johny Antony, Manju Pillai, Kainakary Thankaraj and Naslen K. Gafoor. In the movie, Indrans plays Oliver Twist, Manju Pillai plays Kuttiyamma, Sreenath Bhasi plays Antony, Naslen K. Gafoor plays Charles, and Kainakary Thankaraj plays Appachan. The plot revolves around an old father, Oliver Twist, who is a technologically challenged man, while his sons, on the other hand, stay updated about all the latest technologies and are tech geeks. The movie follows a regular middle-class family and has a slice of life attributed to it. This movie is very well suited to be called "family-friendly", which every person in the family can enjoy watching. It is perfect for watching with your whole family and has many heartwarming moments. The film was released on Amazon Prime and can be watched anytime. 2. Kumbalangi Nights ( 2019) Another Malayalam drama-based film. Syam Pushkaran served as the film's writer, and Madhu C. Narayanam was the director of the movie. Fahadh Faasil, Nazriya Nazim, Syam Pushkaran, and Dileesh Pothan worked together in order to produce the film. The main casting of the film includes Shane Nigam playing Bobby Napoleon, Soubin Shahir playing Saji Napoleon, Mathew Thomas playing Franky Napoleon, Fahadh Faasil playing Shammi Sreenivasan, and Sreenath Bhasi playing Bonny Napoleon. The movie is about 4 brothers who share a love-hate relationship with each other, who, even after multiple different events throughout the film, eventually stand up for the family. The movie was commercially successful, considering the budget it was made with. Surely worth your time, it has been rated very positively by many and is considered a great movie which is a high scorer in all departments of a movie. The film claimed many awards, including NETPAC Award, 2 SIIMA awards, 3 Asianet film Awards, 4 Kerela State Film Awards, and multiple others. It was listed under Best Malayalam Films of the Decade by many reputed publications. 3. Drishyam 2 (2021) You will like this one if you are a fan of thriller elements in films. It was written and directed by Jeethu Joseph. The film's producer is Antony Perumbavoor. As the name suggests, this film is a sequel to the 2013 film "Drishyam". The main cast of this movie includes Mohanlal as Georgekutty, Meena as Rani George, who is Goergekutty's wife, Ansiba Hassan as his elder daughter Anju George, Esther Anil as the younger daughter Anu George, Saikumar as Vinayachandran, Siddique as Prabhakar, Murali Gopi as Thomas Bastin, and Asha Sharath as Geeta Prabhakar. The plot follows in continuation from Drishyam and presents the story of George Kutty doing everything he can to protect his family from the investigation. It is strongly recommended by everyone who has watched it and has gotten many positive reviews after Drishyam. The sequel did not disappoint and lived up to its expectations. 4. Premam (2015) A perfect movie for those looking to find some comedy and romance elements together. Alphonse Puthren has written and directed the film, while Anwar Rasheed is the producer. The story mainly revolves around two characters - George David, played by Nivin Pauly, and Malar, played by Sai Pallavi. The Sai Pallavi won Best Female Debut and Best Male Playback Singer awards at the 63rd Filmfare Awards South while scoring a nomination in 5 other categories as well. The film also got listing in the Best Malayalam Films of the Decade. The film shows the transition from teen to adulthood, where the male lead, George, falls in love with Malar, his lecturer. It was a well-liked movie with very positive reviews. The film even got a Telugu remake in 2016 with the same name. 5. Maheshinte Prathikaaram ( 2016) You will find a mix of comedy and drama in this movie. Dileesh Pothan made his debut as a director with this film. Aashiq Abu produces it. The main cast of the film comprises Fahadh Faasil as Mahesh - a photographer and also the owner of Bhavana Studio, Aparna Balamurali as Jimsy Augustine, Alencier Ley Lopez as Baby, Anusree as Soumya, and Shoubin Shahir as Crispin. Syam Pushkaran wrote the story. The story of the movie followed Mahesh - a photographer, trying to sort out a dispute between his friend and a few youngsters. He faces embarrassment upon being knocked to the ground and getting defeated. He then vows not to wear his slippers until he gets revenge for the humiliation he has faced. It received overwhelming praise for its humour, cinematography, screenplay, and the performances everyone had presented. It won multiple awards like Best Original Screenplay and Best Feature Film Malayalam at the 64th National Film Awards and also won two more awards during the 47th Kerela State Film Awards. The film got a Tamil and a Telugu remake as Nimir in 2018, and Uma Maheshwara Ugra Roopasya in 2020, respectively. 6. Jana Gana Mana ( 2022) A thriller Malayalam film with political aspects in it. The movie was directed by Dijo Jose Antony and was written by Sharis Mohammed. Supriya Menon and Listin Stephen jointly produced the movie. The main cast of the movie includes Prithviraj Sukumaran as DCP Aravind Swaminathan, Suraj Venjaramoodu as ACP Sajjan Kumar, Pasupathi Raj as Moorthy, G.M. Sundar as Nageshwar Rao, and Mamta Mohandas as Sabe Mariyam. The story follows the student unrest of college students caused by the brutal murder of a professor, which is then investigated by ACP Sajjan Kumar while Adv./ DCP Aravind Swaminathan seeks justice in the court. The movie received immense positive reviews and was praised for the narrative style and performance of the cast. The movie was also confirmed to have a sequel in the making. 7. The Great Indian Kitchen ( 2021) This drama film was written and directed by Jeo Baby. The film was produced by Dijo Augustine, Jomon Jacob, Vishnu Rajan, and Sajin S Raj jointly. The main leads of the film are Nimisha Sajayan and Suraj Venjaramoodu, playing the roles of the wife, who is also a dancer, and the husband, respectively. The story revolves around the wife's struggles in the family and her sufferings, where she is supposed to be a submissive woman. Over the course of the film, she faces many challenges and is prevented from pursuing her dream as a dancer until, one day, she breaks free for the sake of her freedom and her dreams. Apart from being an amazing movie, the film also throws light on the ill-treatment of women in backward households. The film received critical praise and won awards like the Kerela State Film Award for Best Film, Best Sound Designer and Best Screenplay. The movie is a very well-developed piece of work, which one should definitely watch. 8. Android Kunjappan Version 5.25 (2019) If you like sci-fi movies, then you will enjoy this one a lot. It is a mixture of sci-fi, drama and comedy meshed perfectly. The film was written by Ratheesh Balakrishnan Poduval and directed by him as well, making it his directorial debut. Santhosh T. Kuruvilla produced the movie. The main cast of the film consists of Suraj Venjaramoodu, Soubin Shahir, Sooraj Thelakkad, Saiju Kurup, and Kendy Zirdo. The story follows Subrahmanyan (Soubin Shahir), who has to leave India and go to Russia in order to get the job offer he received and pursue his dreams. His father, Bhaskaran Poduval (Suraj Venjaramoodu), who is very old age needs someone to take care of him, so his son leaves him with an Android Robot called Kunjappan (Sooraj Thelakkad), but his father is against the idea as he wanted his son to be by his side and not go for any jobs during his last days. However, later on in the movie, Poduval develops a very close bond with the robot, and it becomes an irreplaceable part of his life. The movie won three Kerela State Film Awards and also received great praise for everyone's performance; and was titled one of the best films released in the year 2019. Suraj's performance was heavily praised in the movie and regarded as o